 Posts: 326<br> <font color=#333333>(2/6/03 2:06:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=422.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Mages would have to be overpowered...</span><hr size=1> to anywhere near the same degree that enchanters/shamans currently are and monks were in order to be deserving of a nerf, right now there simply not. Enchanters and shamans have been overpowered for a very long time, as someone who has played both and the mage class all to 65 I can say that imo its not even very close right now(mage charm discounted cause I seriously see it being nerfed into oblvion as it should be). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=balanzsonofanz>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 2848<br> <font color=#333333>(2/6/03 3:25:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=422.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mages would have to be overpowered...</span><hr size=1> No work at all, really, but I confess the reason that I put it into rants is it seemed to me, upon first reading, as a somewhat subtle form of trolling, to stir up mages to no good purpose.  Revenge, perhaps, from some angry enchanter, to attack one of our abilities in retaliation for our discussions of charm.<br>
<br>
I used to think that chaining pets made improvements to innate elemental strength nigh impossible.  History proved me wrong.<br>
<br>
I do not think cannibalization is a problem for mages.  I have argued elsewhere that it is fair, balanced, and not an exploit:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://forums.crgaming.com/eqbb/viewtopic.php?t=77674">Reclaiming pets for mana, a balanced approached</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Verant</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> has given us far too many abilities in support of this for me to believe they do not approve.<br>
<br>
However, I do think that the cost of being petless must remain high in order to balance this ability.  Thus I am against root, snare, or stun, except indirectly through pets <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>(I think giving the post-50 fire pet snare might be a good idea)</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
I rarely am able to reclaim pets for mana in a group, except during high down time <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>(CRs, forced med breaks after overpulls, etc.)</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  Soloing, it serves to reduce down time.  It is nearly useless in a fight, except for multi-<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>IRE</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> mage groups, which is highly specialized application.<br>
<br>
I do not think reclaiming pets for mana is a problem that needs to be solved.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Raz</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fethy>fethy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#333333>(2/6/03 3:50:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=422.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mages would have to be overpowered...</span><hr size=1> I'll be honest, I'm no Chanter, <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . My main is actually a Shaman. I was certainly unhappy with SoE's lame public relations of the past two days, and vented a bit. <br>
<br>
I don't want Mages changed at all, on the contrary, I have a Mage myself. Hence why you have seen some posts on this board from me. But I worry if I did put in the effort to get the Mage where I wanted him, he'd only be changed in ways you didn't plan your eq life around. And having some Mages brag on like the Monk board about what they can do, without having some insane gear you need to be uber guilded for, seems to be shooting the Mage class in the foot. Granted, they would have to change the Necro class as well, as they fall in the same general category.<br>
<br>
Lifting other classes up is usually better then bringing others down, unless it's really something totally out of whack, which pet canni isn't with it's major limitations.<br>
<br>
I don't consider myself a troll, but I was a bit hot headed at the time, and wanted some opinions. I think even if I did stoop to real troll level, I'm smart enough to not make it to obvious. But even if I come off as that way a bit, it's not my intention really. and you'll never see me flame anyone. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tangting01>TangTing01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 173<br> <font color=#333333>(2/6/03 2:04:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=422.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mages would have to be overpowered...</span><hr size=1> Balanz, looks like your first paragraph hit the nail on the head.     <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gurglespitfruggybasher>Gurglespit Fruggybasher</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://dyce.i8.com/gurblip.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 119<br> <font color=#333333>(2/6/03 3:50:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=422.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mages would have to be overpowered...</span><hr size=1> Read Balanz's article.. it explains it very well and I have to agree with his thoughts that this is now an intended ability of mages (maybe it wasn't in the beginning... but I do think it is now)<br>
